race.comment: FLIRT (15) returns for the Bain & Taylor partnership and looks to have come back in terrific order, piecing together two sharp pieces of work in readiness. Holder sticks from his jumpout and a bright return is anticipated. ONE WHIM (4) makes his stable debut for the Hickmott camp and has been gelded during the break. His lead-up work suggests he's taken great improvement and can return with a bang. CAMOOWEAL GIRL (12) warmed nicely to her task late on debut at Murray Bridge and is sure to have come on with that run under her belt, though she'll need luck from the horror draw. Expect her to be charging late. BEL HOTESSE (7) continues to find the maiden win elusive but has runs scattered through her form that measure up. Draws well and is worth keeping safe.
